Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice one-quarter of the @red onion{1}(thinly sliced);
dice remaining onion. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve @green bell pepper{2} lengthwise;
remove stems and seeds. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the lime
(whole lime for 4 servings), @sugar{1/4%tsp} (1⁄2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of
@salt{pinch}. Microwave until onion is bright pink, ~{30%seconds}. Set aside.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}
(11⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

While rice cooks, place green peppers on a #baking sheet{} and drizzle each half
with @cooking oil{5%teaspoon}; rub all over to coat. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then arrange cut sides down. Roast on top rack until browned and
softened, ~{18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over
medium-high heat. Add diced onion and season with salt and pepper. Cook,
stirring, until softened, ~{5%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, garlic, and @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon};
season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is
browned and cooked through, ~{6%minutes}.

> Swap in ground turkey for beef.

Stir in @tomato paste{1%unit}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and
@water{1/3%cup} (1⁄2 cup for 4 servings). Reduce heat to medium low and simmer
until mixture is slightly thickened, ~{2%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a fork and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}. Add to pan with beef
mixture and stir until thoroughly combined; season with salt and pepper.

Once green peppers are done roasting, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully
flip and stuff halves with up to half the filling (save the rest for serving).
Nestle each stuffed pepper in pan with remaining filling.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer stuffed peppers and filling to a baking
> dish now.

Evenly sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Transfer pan to top rack
and roast until cheese melts, ~{4%minutes}.

Divide remaining filling between plates. Top with stuffed peppers and as much
pickled onion (draining first) as you like.

Dollop with @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tablespoon} and serve with any remaining
lime wedges on the side.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.